en:{'nav.model':'Model','nav.processes':'Processes','nav.graph':'Graph','nav.pages':'Pages','hero.title':'Visual map of the Before We Build LLM Wiki','hero.lead':'Before We Build is a research framework where Socionics, Action-and-decision map and Temporistics are used as heuristic languages for hypotheses about latent processes: information, action and temporal/existential experience.','hero.cta':'View model','hero.note':'Not a proven science claim and not a source of final compatibility answers: types here are working hypotheses that require validation.','model.title':'Three levels: strategic, operational, tactical','model.intro':'Before We Build groups information around three levels, not one label: where a person is going, how they organize action, and how they model situations.','pipeline.title':'From observation to validation','pipeline.text':'Before We Build separates observable behavior from hypotheses about hidden processes. The site presents this logic as a research pipeline, not final personality labels.','processes.title':'Processes inside each level','processes.intro':'Each level has a primary process: strategic works with time and meaning, operational with action organization, tactical with information modeling.','processes.strategic.title':'Strategic · Temporistics','processes.strategic.tag':'Induction ↔ deduction in time and meaning','processes.strategic.text':'How experience becomes a pattern, and a pattern becomes an expectation, scenario or meaning interpretation.','processes.operational.title':'Operational · Action-and-decision map','processes.operational.tag':'Analysis ↔ synthesis in action','processes.operational.text':'How a task is broken into parts and then assembled into a decision, coordination pattern or action.','processes.tactical.title':'Tactical · Socionics','processes.tactical.tag':'Information modeling','processes.tactical.text':'How signals, facts and context are linked into an internal model of the situation: “what is happening here?”','disclaimer':'Before We Build is a research framework and hypothesis generator, not a diagnostic tool and not a validated source of final compatibility answers.','process3d.title':'3D model of complex processes','process3d.text':'The canvas visualization shows Before We Build as a space of three axes: information, action and temporal/existential meaning. Nodes are wiki concepts and hypotheses; lines are proposed links between observations, typological patterns and validation.','process3d.orbit':'Orbit','process3d.layers':'Layers','process3d.flow':'Flow','process3d.caption':'No backend: you can drag with mouse/touch, and the animation renders directly in the browser.','graph.title':'Mini graph of key pages','graph.text':'The first prototype visualizes starting wiki nodes. The next step is automatic graph generation from markdown files and wikilinks.','graph.all':'All','graph.theory':'Theory','graph.systems':'Systems','pages.title':'Start pages of the LLM Wiki',pipeline:['observable traces','typological pattern hypothesis','latent process hypothesis','compatibility / role-fit prediction','validation and recalibration'],levels:[['01','Strategic','Temporistics','var(--color-primary)','induction/deduction in temporal and existential experience','Main question: do we share a compatible life trajectory, meaning and horizon?','Time · meaning · past/present/future · life scenario'],['02','Operational','Action-and-decision map','var(--color-warning)','synthesis and analysis in action','Main question: can we organize decisions, effort and action together?','Priorities · will · logic · emotion · physics · coordination'],['03','Tactical','Socionics','var(--color-accent)','information modeling / information metabolism','Main question: do our perception and information-exchange interfaces fit?','Signals · interpretation · communication · situational understanding']],pages:[['main-idea','Main Idea','The central Before We Build formula and three compatibility levels.'],['project-positioning','Project Positioning','Before We Build as a research framework, not only a dating product.'],['latent-process','Latent Process','How to separate observable traces from hypotheses about hidden processes.'],['compatibility-level-boundaries','Compatibility Level Boundaries','Boundaries between Temporistics, Action-and-decision map and Socionics.'],['weight-calibration','Weight Calibration','Why compatibility weights need empirical calibration.'],['intertype-relation-naming-audit','Relation Naming Audit','Audit of relation names and mechanisms.']]},
